### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

compiler

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Hi friends! I apologize if this has already been reported or if this is not the correct repo.

When I add `"typeCheckHostBindings": true` to my tsconfig.json, I get some errors trying to compile my application.

If I bind to just `keydown`, this code appears to be perfectly-typed:

```
@Directive({
  host: {
    '(keydown)': 'onKeydown($event)'
  },
})
export class ValidDirective {
  protected onKeydown(_: KeyboardEvent): void {}
}
```

However, if I bind to a specific key, I get error TS2345 and this code no longer compiles:

```
@Directive({
  host: {
    '(keydown.enter)': 'onKeydown($event)'
  },
})
export class InvalidDirective {
  protected onKeydown(_: KeyboardEvent): void {}
}
```

I am able to change some of my callback functions to the more generic `Event` type to appease the compiler, but it feels wrong because if I log the event, the browser reveals that it is actually in fact of type `KeyboardEvent`.

